<br>
2 Wizards, one 53+ and one 56+<br>
2 Enchanters - both 53+<br>
1 Cleric - 54+<br>
1 Bard or Paladin - 55+<br>
<br>
2 enchanters is key.  You can really boost the average pull size and its much less strain on the enchanters.  You will die less.<br>
<br>
2 wizzies.  Using Jylls they can do enough damage to take out pretty much all Karnor/Sebilis mobs you are going to be pulling.  Thunderclap is great for &quot;herding&quot; your prey into a more easy to manage group, closer to the chanters.  56+ is good because the wiz will have more than one Jylls and kill time will be reduced.<br>
<br>
1 cleric.  Cleric is good for keeping the chanters alive, but also can AE nuke to polish off the extra tough mobs.<br>
<br>
1 bard/paladin.  Both have their plusses.  I believe bards have an AE tash that can really help the stuns land, and mana cantana for reducing downtime.  Paladins have great survivability and can heal as well. <br>
<br>
cheers,<br>
Asiago<br>
55 Evoker<br>
The Seventh Hammer<br>
<br>
